RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPUN BEAUTIFUL showed speed away from the start and assumed command in the early stages, set a quick pace while on a clear lead into the turn, carved out fast fractions from the two path heading to the quarter marker, widened the lead into the stretch, was kept to moderate urging into the final sixteenth and was hand ridden to the finish. MISS SKI broke a step slowly away from the gate, was asked to show early speed and chased the fast pace to the turn, saved ground along the bend, angled to the four path into upper stretch, closed well inside of the furlong marker, could not impact the winner in deep stretch and was up in time to secure second. O'NEILL'S LEGACY tracked the solid pace from a two wide position, chased SPUN BEAUTIFUL to the quarter marker and tipped three wide for the stretch drive, lost ground at the furlong marker, re-bid in the final sixteenth but was outfinished for second in the final strides and held safely in the end for third. HOW ABOUT A FRESCA settled off of the solid early pace, saved ground into the turn, was steered two wide approaching the top of the stretch, closed in the final stages but could not muster the needed late response and missed for third. SHOUT IT OUT tracked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, swung five wide for the stretch drive and finished evenly in the final furlong. COASTAL STARLITE lacked early speed, raced in the two path to the quarter marker, was gaining in the stretch but was unable to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: How About a Fresca
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside,tipped 2wide stretch,closed,needed more late

ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow,chased ins,angled 4wide into stretch,closed,up 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked 2wide,3wide into stretch,outkicked,lost 2nd,held 3rd

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked outside,swung 5wide stretch,finished evenly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 6F All Weather Track CR: 77. Claiming Purse 13400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MADE THE TEAM vied for the early lead with EDDIE CROSSWIRE leaving the break, took command in the opening furlong and set a solid pace into the turn, showed speed along the bend while carving quick fractions and extended the lead while in hand into upper stretch, was kept to task under steady urging into the final sixteenth and was geared down in deep stretch to prevail as much the best. CAMZUL tracked the early pace from the inside, was coaxed along from the rail into upper stretch, was not able to impact the winner in the final furlong but offered a mild late bid and was up in the final strides to secure second. EDDIE CROSSWIRE contested the early lead leaving the break then pressed MADE THE TEAM into the turn, lost a bit of ground while two wide along the bend, chased MADE THE TEAM into the stretch, weakened in the final sixteenth and was edged for second, while well clear for third. G'S LAST CHANCE hopped at the start and was off a step slowly, chased the early pace while outside of runners, came three wide to the quarter marker, lost ground approaching the furlong pole and lacked a late response. YOU KIDDING ME lacked early speed, saved ground into the turn, swung to the four path for the stretch drive and did not factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Camzul
ENTRY.OWNER: Mad Hansen Racing LLC and Sandlot Racing Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside,mild late bid,up for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: You Kidding Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: no early speed,swung four wide stretch,no factor

ENTRY.NAME: G's Last Chance
ENTRY.OWNER: Thompson Gary A and Thompson Linda J
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start,chased 3wide,lost ground 1/8,no late response

ENTRY.NAME: Made the Team
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied early,took command,showed speed turn,drew away stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Eddie Crosswire
ENTRY.OWNER: Bellasis Tim Smartt Donna and Tschanz Cassandra

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 6F All Weather Track CR: 78. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Races Where Entered For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered For The Optional Claiming Pri ce).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILD JEWELS contested the early lead with UNION COACH then assumed command in the opening furlong, set a decent pace into the turn, rated nicely along the bend and was well handled to the top of the stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong marker and drew away while under a hand ride in the final stages to be much the best. UNION COACH broke alertly and vied for the early lead with WILD JEWELS, ceded the lead to that rival and tracked the pace from the three path into the turn, advanced while two wide heading to the quarter marker, could not match strides with WILD JEWELS into the stretch, was no match for the winner in the final furlong and was best of the rest. DRUM BUNNY was bumped at the start and was away a bit slowly, chased from the rear in the early stages, was coaxed two wide along the turn, swung three wide for the stretch run, was not able to impact the top two in the final furlong and ran on late for third. AUTISM PUZZLE chased the early pace from the inside, improved position on the turn, was asked for run in upper stretch, lacked a response inside of the furlong marker and gave way in the final sixteenth. CORAL CAT tracked the early pace from the second flight, chased three wide along the turn and gained ground nearing the quarter marker, was guided four wide into the stretch, dropped back approaching the furlong marker and tired in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Drum Bunny
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start,2wide turn,3wide stretch,ran on for 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Autism Puzzle
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,gain 1/4,no response stretch,gave way late

ENTRY.NAME: Coral Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked,chased 3wide turn,gain 1/4,4wide into stretch,tired

ENTRY.NAME: Wild Jewels
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace,well handled turn,clear 1/8,drew away,handily,much best

ENTRY.NAME: Union Coach
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,vied early,tracked 3w-2w,no match for winner,2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 5F Turf CR: 84. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THREEBROTHERS broke a step slowly, rushed up in the early stages and stalked the decent pace from the inside, saved ground along the turn and waited for racing room nearing the quarter marker, angled three wide into the stretch, advanced in upper stretch and was full of run approaching the furlong pole, collared the runner-up heading to the sixteenth-marker and drew clear under hand urging to prevail in a good debut. CARDINAL TRICK was away in good order leaving the start, engaged with DRIVER'S ED in the early stages and disputed the decent pace with that rival into the turn, dueled through moderate fractions along the bend, battled with DRIVER'S ED into upper stretch and took a narrow lead at the furlong marker, was collared by THREEBROTHERS approaching the sixteenth-marker, could not match strides with the winner in deep stretch and just held for second at the finish. STOUT tracked the decent early pace while outside of rivals, was steered to the two path entering the turn, swung five wide for the stretch drive and ran evenly to the furlong marker, rallied in deep stretch and just missed for second at the finish, while clear of the rest for third. DRIVER'S ED was asked for speed leaving the start, engaged with CARDINAL TRICK in the early stages and contested decent fractions with that rival into the turn, dueled from the inside along the bend while carving out a moderate pace, battled with CARDINAL TRICK into the stretch and fought back to the furlong marker, came up empty in deep stretch and weakened in the final stages. WEE BEASTIE was prominent in the early running and stalked the decent pace while outside of rivals, raced close to the pace while three wide approaching the quarter marker, was floated four wide into upper stretch, could not keep pace heading to the furlong marker and tired in the late stages. MY BUCKET LIST was a bit slow into stride leaving the start, was hard to place while trailing in the early stages, was steered to the outside heading into the turn, lugged out along the turn and did not factor in the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: D K Racing LLC Radley Equine Inc Wine Alot Stables Daw Edward Gold Rick Hindman
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,dueled pace,battled stretch,weakened late

ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow early,hard to place,lugged out turn,no factor

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled pace,battled stretch,led 1/8,caught 1/16,held 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: close up 3wide,floated 4wide 3/16,lost ground 1/8,tired late

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked outside,swung 5wide stretch,rallied,just missed 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 6F All Weather Track CR: 70. Claiming Purse 13400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THREAD COUNT was prominent in the early running, stalked the solid pace into the turn then advanced along the bend and pressed the pace while two wide nearing the quarter marker, was roused at the top of the stretch and took a narrow lead heading to the furlong grounds, shook free approaching the sixteenth-marker and drew away while kept to task in the final stages. JERSEY STAR broke alertly, rated off of the decent early pace and tracked into the turn, raced three wide to the quarter marker and was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, closed well in deep stretch, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and was up in time to secure second. WHATWASTHENISNOW was hustled to establish the early lead, set a solid pace while pressured into the turn, was pressed by THREAD COUNT heading to the quarter marker and battled with that rival into upper stretch, fought back from the inside approaching the furlong pole, weakened in the final sixteenth and was outfinished for second, while clear in the end for third. BLUE BREEZE was unhurried in the early running, was coaxed along in the four path along the turn, swung five wide for the stretch drive, showed good late interest but was unable to impact the leaders in deep stretch. LUCKY LOCKETT chased the fast early pace, went two wide between rivals along the turn, was steered three wide into the stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker and gave way in the final sixteenth. TIME TO SMILE was forwardly placed in the early stages and tracked the solid pace from the inside, lost ground on the turn, stayed to the inside into upper stretch, was outrun to the furlong marker and faded in the final stages. EXTREME BLAZE stalked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, came three wide into the turn and lost ground nearing the quarter marker, trailed into the stretch and came up empty in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Time to Smile
ENTRY.COMMENT: forward,tracked inside,lost ground turn,faded stretch

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,btwn 2wide turn,3wide stretch,lost ground 1/8,gave way

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly,took back,4wide into stretch,closed well late,up 2d

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace 3wide,lost ground 1/4,empty stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 6F All Weather Track CR: 78. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In E ligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY GREGORY was asked for speed leaving the break and set a contested early pace, shook free heading into the turn and set solid fractions to the quarter marker, repelled the bid of HANNAH IN A HURRY in upper stretch and drew to a clear lead approaching the furlong marker, was kept to task under steady urging into the final sixteenth and pulled away in deep stretch to prevail. HANNAH IN A HURRY was a bit reluctant to load prior to the start, was prominent in the early running and pressed the solid pace from a two wide path, lost ground to LADY GREGORY along the turn and stalked that rival to the quarter marker, was turned away in upper stretch and chased LADY GREGORY to the furlong pole, could not impact the winner in the final sixteenth and ran on to be second best. KITTEN'S KID tracked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, chased three wide along the turn, lost ground into upper stretch, could not match strides with the top two in the final furlong and weakened late, while holding for third. MARY MARGARET was squeezed by neighboring rivals at the start and was off a bit slowly, raced in tight while between rivals into the turn, gave chase from the two path along the bend, swung to the six path into upper stretch, was able to offer a mild late bid but needed more in the final stages. GET'EM TIGER tracked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, chased four wide to the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch and gave way. LILA AT THE BEACH stalked the quick early pace from the inside, lost ground along the turn, angled to the two path into upper stretch, could not keep pace heading to the furlong grounds and tired in the late stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Gregory
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed,repelled foe 3/16,clear 1/8,pulled away late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1M All Weather Track CR: 81. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAM'S TIME raced near the front of the pack tracking far behind the runaway pacesetter, came under a ride with three furlongs to go, made a steady rally down the lane and was along in time. ZOOKEEPER broke out and forced DARK MYSTERY into SIPPIN WHISKEY, went straight to the front, opened up a long lead while always travelling well, was still well clear of the rest going into the stretch, began to tire a bit in the final sixteenth and was just caught in the shadow of the wire. DE LA LUNA was not asked for speed from the break, got hung four wide into the first turn, moved up to the front of the tracking group by the half mile marker, was set down approaching the three furlong pole, matched strides with TAM'S TIME to mid-stretch, was outkicked in the final stages and held clearly for third. APLOMBADO broke well, got over to the rail and was near the front of the tracking pack to the half, tipped out a path on the far turn to start a mild rally from the seven-sixteenths marker, finished with some interest down the stretch but came up short of a minor award. PORT O' CALL allowed to settle from the start, raced three wide near the back of the pack through the clubhouse turn, stayed wide but in the clear down the backstretch, made a brief rally from the three eighths pole, came four wide into the lane, showed good late interest but was unable to impact the leaders. ONE LITTLE INDIAN raced near the head of the tracking group and remained prominent to the far turn, could not keep up when the pace quickened from the three eighths pole, tried to re-bid on the rail down the stretch but could not summon the needed response. SIPPIN WHISKEY broke in a little and avoided any contact but was then bumped off stride a few jumps out of the gate by DARK MYSTERY, was content to settle in the middle of the tracking group through the early stages but was done before the stretch and ridden out to the wire. DARK MYSTERY broke out a bit at the start then was forced into SIPPIN WHISKEY when ZOOKEEPER came over, angled sharply to the rail then was steadied when put in tight into the first turn, was boxed in and a little hard to place around that turn, settled down for the backstretch run but could do no better than chase the field home from that point.

ENTRY.OWNER: Bran Jam Stable California Racing Partners Ciaglia Racing LLC and Drenk Robert
ENTRY.COMMENT: opened up long lead in hand, tired late, tagged at the line

ENTRY.NAME: Dark Mystery
ENTRY.COMMENT: roughed up start, steadied, boxed 1st, chased, no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Sippin Whiskey
ENTRY.OWNER: Gust Charles and Warren John P
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped after start, settled mid-pack, no bid, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Port o' Call
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle 3w, brief rally 3/8, stalled, one-paced

ENTRY.NAME: Aplombado
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, saved ground, tipped 2p rally, some late interest

ENTRY.NAME: One Little Indian
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked to far turn, lost ground 3/8, lacked needed response

ENTRY.NAME: Tam's Time
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked from far behind, steady rally from 3/8, up in time

ENTRY.NAME: De la Luna
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4wide first turn, set down 3/8, bid stretch, outkicked,clear 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1M All Weather Track CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TITOS WITH A TWIST was hustled to the front then gained the lead through the first turn, opened a clear lead approaching the half mile marker, held that lead through the far turn while travelling very well in hand, responded to intermittent urging down the stretch and was pulling away at the end. SON OF SHANGHAI pushed forward from the gate but was outrun to the turn by TITOS WITH A TWIST, was a bit keen through the first turn while in tight quarters, backed off a bit while saving ground down the backstretch, re-engaged the leaders heading into the far turn, rallied into the second spot at the top of the stretch, could not reel in the winner but held the place. THE SLAP outrun from the break, lagged at the rear of the field, started making some forward progress from the half mile marker then made an eye catching sweeping move wide through the turn, got into contention at the top of the stretch and sustained the move to just miss for second, while just getting up for third. BALLROOM PRINCE was hustled from the gate but got outrun to the turn, settled in mid-pack down the backstretch, was well placed into the far turn and saved ground into upper stretch, lacked a final response in deep stretch and just missed for the minor awards. UPDRAFT broke well and was able to get over to the two path into the first turn, advanced to challenge TITOS WITH A TWIST for the lead entering the backstretch while under some restraint, let that one get away from the half then came under a drive from the three-eighths marker and weakened in the stretch. LAURA'S KIDOUGH checked off heels after the break then checked again going into the first turn, was keen along the first turn and floated out a rival heading into the backstretch run, raced mid-pack down the backstretch under some restraint, made a brief bid from the three-eighths pole, was steered into the five path into upper stretch and gave way in the late stages. FANTASTIC DREAM settled off of the early pace and raced outside of rivals into the first turn, was floated four wide along the first turn and maintained a wide trip into the backstretch run, was coaxed along in the three path entering the far turn, could not keep pace heading to the quarter marker and tired in the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Ballroom Prince
ENTRY.COMMENT: outrun to turn, settled mid-pack,inside,needed more late

ENTRY.NAME: Son of Shanghai
ENTRY.OWNER: Kelly Benjamin E and Taylor Faith
ENTRY.COMMENT: in tight 1st turn, saved ground to stretch, rallied, held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Titos With a Twist
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled to lead, opened up in hand 1/2, pulled away late

ENTRY.NAME: Laura's Kidough
ENTRY.COMMENT: took up start,keen 1st turn,3wide-5wide,gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Fantastic Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled,floated 4wide 1st,3wide 2nd turn,tired stretch

ENTRY.NAME: The Slap
ENTRY.OWNER: California Racing Partners Ciaglia Racing LLC and Pearson Richard C
ENTRY.COMMENT: outrun early, lagged to 1/2, big move turn, gained third

ENTRY.NAME: Updraft
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace early, lost ground turn, weakened stretch
